text: Olympic National Park is a national park in the U.S. state of Washington. It was established on June 29, 1938. The park covers nearly of the Olympic Peninsula and covers most of the Olympic Mountains. The western part of the national park is the wettest place in the contiguous United States (outside Hawaii and Alaska). == References == == Other websites == Category:20th- century establishments in Washington (state) Category:1938 establishments in the United States Category:National parks in the United States Category:Biosphere reserves Category:Forests of the United States Category:World Heritage Sites in the United States Category:Geography of Washington (state)
